title.narrative: OUTPUT 4.1: PRE-PRIMARY EDUCATION

description.narrative: Output 4.1: By 2019, pre-primary school aged girls and boys have increased access to quality education services and improved learning achievement, especially those in districts/counties with education indicators less than the national average. (UNDAF 3.2.1), which contributes to Early Learning, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Learning Outcomes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 4 By 2019, school aged girls and boys have increased access to quality education services and improved learning achievement, especially those in districts/counties below the national average. (UNDAF 1.3.2.1)

description.narrative: By October 2019, a total of 8,266 children (4,003 girls, 4,263 boys) out of school children participated in learning and a total of 7,204 pre-primary children (3,532 girls and 3,672 boys) at the right age (3–5 years) had accessed quality early learning in four underserved counties because of the increased capacity of 75 ECD county-level facilitators and 2,008 (1,104 females, 904 males) teachers/caregivers to interpret and apply the ECD policy and curriculum | Status:Met | As-of Date:26/12/2019
